            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab><persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/320">Walprand</persName> in
                        Dei nomine <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>, quia ex iussione domni nostri
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/48">Aistulfi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">regis</rs> directus sum in <rs key="#Army"
                            >exercito</rs> ambulandum cum ipso. Unde dispensare previdi de <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">omnibus rebus meis</rs> ut, dum advivere
                        meruero, omnia in mea sit potestate (…); et si mihi occasio mortis
                        obvenerit, volo ut omnes res meas que iniudicata vel non vinduta aut non
                        donata remanserit, duas partes habeat <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                            >eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, ubi nunc presenti ego pontifex esse videor; et
                        taliter volo, ut una pars de ipse duo portionis, quas in eclesia Sancti
                        Martini feci, debeat esse in <orgName key="#Hospitals"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/132"><rs key="#Hospitals"
                            >senodochio</rs></orgName> qui a domno <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/313">Talesperiano</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopo</rs> hic fore <rs key="#Walls">muro</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/4" key="#Cities #Walls"><rs key="#Cities"
                                >civitatis</rs></placeName> constructum est; et tertiam partem
                        habeat <rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Relics" ref="#juridical_persons/70">Sancti
                            Fridiani</orgName>, ubi ipse <rs key="#Relics">sanctus corpus
                            requiescit</rs>; et quarta parte habeat <rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/256">Sancte
                            Reparate</orgName>, ubi <persName key="#Other_clerics #Priors"><name
                                ref="Garimundus">Garimundus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Priors">custor</rs> esse videtur, <foreign>affinché i preti di
                            dette chiese preghino per lui</foreign>. <rs key="#Slave">Servos autem
                            meos vel ancillas</rs> volo ut liveri omnes esse debeant et a ius
                        patronati absoluti, sicut illi homines qui ex nubile genere procreati et
                        nati esse videntur. <foreign>Chi si opponga o i preti che non pregassero per
                            lui siano sottoposti al giudizio divino</foreign>. Et vos fratres meos
                            <persName ref="#people/386">Perprand</persName> et <persName
                            ref="#people/387">Pertifuns</persName>, volo ut habeatis parte me de <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">pecunia</rs> nostra in <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions">Corsica</placeName> in integrum; et in hoc
                        sitits contempti. <foreign>Se Walprando tornasse salvo dalla guerra, il
                            testamento sia annullato. Scrive</foreign>: <persName
                            key="#Writer #Subdeacons"><name ref="Osprandus"
                            >Osprando</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiacono</rs> nostro. (…) Actum in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/4">Luca</placeName>, in <orgName
                            key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68">domo sacnte
                            eclesie</orgName>. Et quod menime recordatus sum, quicquid indivisum de
                        rebus meis remanserit, aut per quocumque ingenio mihi legibus pertenet,
                        mobile vel inmobile, volo ut, sicut supra legitur, in suprascriptas eclesias
                        debeat esse potestate; sic tamen, ut supra dixi, post decesso meo in eo
                        ordine permaneat. <foreign>Sottoscrizioni</foreign>: Walprand in Dei nomine
                        episcopus (ss); <persName key="#Witness #Deacons"><name ref="Ausbertus"
                                >Ospert</name></persName> exiguus <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>
                        (ss); <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Buccius"
                            >Buccio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs> (ss); <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics #Priors" ref="#people/705"><name ref="Gausbertus"
                                >Gauspertus</name></persName> exiguus <rs key="#Other_clerics"
                            >clericus</rs> et <rs key="#Priors">rector</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">eclesie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/70">Sancti
                            Fridiani</orgName> (ss); + <persName
                            key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name ref="Garimundus"
                                >Garimund</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis; + <persName
                            key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name ref="Gairepertus"
                                >Gairipert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis.
                            <foreign>Copia:</foreign> Ego ipse <persName key="#Copyist #Subdeacons"
                                ><name ref="Osprandus">Osprand</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconus</rs> supradictus scriptor quantum in
                        autenticum inveni, nec plus addendi, nec menime scribsi; et presens exempla
                        data est <persName><name ref="Maurus">Mauri</name></persName>, qui fuit
                        supradicti bone memorie quondam Walprand episcopi. </ab>
